---

## 🧭 5. Incident Response Lifecycle

### 🟡 A. Identification  
- Monitor logs using syslog, IDS, and user reports  
- Initial indicators: abnormal login times, sudden data transfer spikes, email phishing alerts  

### 🔴 B. Containment  
- Disable affected user accounts  
- Isolate compromised systems from the network  
- Stop ongoing malicious activity (e.g., malware execution)

### 🛠️ C. Eradication  
- Remove malware or corrupted files  
- Patch exploited vulnerabilities  
- Reset passwords and update firewall rules  

### 🔁 D. Recovery  
- Restore clean backups  
- Monitor systems closely for 72 hours  
- Re-enable services gradually with testing  

### 🧾 E. Lessons Learned  
- Conduct a full post-incident review within 7 days  
- Update this IRP based on findings  
- Document what worked and what didn’t

